,Recommended,255390,11310295,"Posted: 18 July, 2014",all,Ryne,"8/10 -One of the best platformers out there. This one drew me in from it's art style to it's way of solving puzzles. You get this marker which you can raise platforms, create vines, branches, water waves and more. Not only can you create these things but you can actually draw, cut, pull and push them...like if you wanted to make a circle out of a branch, cut it and then let it roll down a hill you can. It makes really unique and interesting puzzles you won't see anywhere else. This game may seem like a kids game because of it's story but don't let that turn you off from playing it."
76561197968114974,Recommended,255390,10335252,"Posted: 3 June, 2014",all,Lorewin,"Relaxing and enchanting, with excellent controls.  (And occasional moments of frantic timing).Max is beautifully animated, with a stronger focus on puzzles than platforming;  in most areas you're constructing your own ""platforms"" made of earth, branches, vines or (the most fun) water, in order to progress.The world has fixed points where you can spawn the different items by ""drawing"" them with your magic marker.  This does mean that typically there's only a single approach to a problem, but it keeps the game flowing nicely; you're unlikely to be stuck for too long on an area, and if you are the checkpoints are very forgiving.  (Getting the optional collectible amulet parts  can involve a little more head scratching).An extra element is added as  branches and vines can be detached from their spawn point and then dragged (or rolled if you managed to draw a circle) around.As a platformer, it's naturally made for the gamepad.  However, I'm playing it with both gamepad and mouse - the mouse really helps when drawing platforms to get the right shape/curve. As you can't move when drawing in any case, the switching between mouse and gamepad is seamless - great work by the devs."
