,Recommended,255390,29949155,Posted: 15 February,all,Increddibelly,"This is a beatiful platformer. It reminds me of Abe's Oddworld, but this is more forgiving.The puzzles consist mostly of physics puzzles that you solve by using a magic marker. The marker extends rocks, grows branches and vines, or shoots water or fire, all from color coded anchor points in the game world. These elements combine beautifully, and you fix the puzzles by being clever and agile. Most levels end in an epic chase / boss / climax.At about 70% through I dropped the gamepad and started using the kb / mouse, which allows for finer control.I wish it were longer."
